text: Presidential elections were held in Kazakhstan for the first time on 1 December 1991.Dieter Nohlen, Florian Grotz & Christof Hartmann (2001) Elections in Asia: A data handbook, Volume I, p 416 Nursultan Nazarbayev won with 99% of the vote, and 88% of the people who could vote actually did. == Results == == References == Category:1991 in Asia
title: 1991 Kazakh presidential election
